Package: r6qualitytools
Type: Package
Title: R6-Based Statistical Methods for Quality Science
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Andrea Barahona, Fabian Encarnacion, Miguel Flores
Maintainer: Andrea Barahona <andrea.barahona@epn.edu.ec>
Description: The package provides a comprehensive suite of statistical tools for Quality Management, designed specifically around the Define, Measure, Analyze, Improve, and Control (DMAIC) cycle used in Six Sigma methodology. This package leverages R6 object-oriented programming for enhanced flexibility and performance, and incorporates modern graphical systems using ggplot2 and plotly for interactive and visually appealing plots. Built on the tidyverse principles, the package simplifies data manipulation and visualization.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
